{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id0d5e7caa-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1096"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1096"},"text":"§ 1096.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administrative expenses","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0d5e7cab-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1096/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Amount of payments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"From the sums appropriated for any fiscal year for the purpose of the program authorized under subpart 1 of part A of this subchapter, the Secretary shall reserve such sums as may be necessary to pay to each institution with which he has an agreement under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1094"},"text":"section 1094 of this title","children":[],"tail":", an amount equal to $5 for each student at that institution who receives assistance under subpart 1 of part A. In addition, an institution which has entered into an agreement with the Secretary under subpart 3 of part A or part C,"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002110"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002110"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original."}],"tail":" of this subchapter or under part E of this subchapter shall be entitled for each fiscal year which such institution disburses funds to eligible students under any such part to a payment for the purpose set forth in subsection (b). The payment for a fiscal year shall be payable from each such allotment by payment in accordance with regulations of the Secretary and shall be equal to 5 percent of the institution’s first $2,750,000 of expenditures plus 4 percent of the institution’s expenditures greater than $2,750,000 and less than $5,500,000, plus 3 percent of the institution’s expenditures in excess of $5,500,000 during the fiscal year from the sum of its grants to students under subpart 3 of part A, its expenditures during such fiscal year under part C for compensation of students, and the principal amount of loans made during such fiscal year from its student loan fund established under part E, excluding the principal amount of any such loans which the institution has referred under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1087cc/a/4/B"},"text":"section 1087cc(a)(4)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":". In addition, the Secretary shall provide for payment to each institution of higher education an amount equal to 100 percent of the costs incurred by the institution in implementing and operating the immigration status verification system under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1091/g"},"text":"section 1091(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0d5e7cac-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1096/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Purpose of payments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0d5e7cad-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1096/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The sums paid to institutions under this part are for the sole purpose of administering the programs described in subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0d5e7cae-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1096/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If the institution enrolls a significant number of students who are (A) attending the institution less than full time, or (B) independent students, the institution shall use a reasonable proportion of the funds available under this section for financial aid services during times and in places that will most effectively accommodate the needs of such students.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id0d5e7caf-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/329/tIV/s489"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–329, title IV, § 489","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/498/tIV/s407/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–498, title IV, § 407(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1491"},"text":"100 Stat. 1491","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/603/tI/s121/b/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–603, title I, § 121(b)(7)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3391"},"text":"100 Stat. 3391","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/50/s15/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–50, § 15(15)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-06-03"},"text":"June 3, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/357"},"text":"101 Stat. 357","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/325/tIV"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–325, title IV","children":[],"tail":", §§ 446(c), 493, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-07-23"},"text":"July 23, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/567"},"text":"106 Stat. 567","children":[],"tai